item.title: 2011 in review
item.description: The WordPress.com stats helper monkeys prepared a 2011 annual report for this blog. Here’s an excerpt: A New York City subway train holds 1,200 people. This blog was viewed about 6,000 times in 2011. If it were a NYC subway train, it would take about 5 trips to carry that many people. Click here to see the complete report.

item.title: Ruby Google Chart API
item.description: A few years ago, I wrote some Ruby code to access the Google Chart API. I’ve (finally) put in up on GitHub. This is part of an effort to get more of my open source projects up in a common space. [https://github.com/willf/ruby_google_charts]2
